name: God of love
description:
From the collection : "inside: Dark sides"

You did not hear me shout
And you did not hear me break
You did not see me collapse
And you did not smell my burning
When the fire engulfed my skirt
And innocent Children of my Love
burned in the fire of your hate
You did not see me
You did not hear me
You did not hug me

And I broke you
like a storm
Like a tornado
like a flood
or a giant wave
I broke you
I burned you
And I knocked you down
As we were both victims of the same religion
And we both bled to death for one God
The God of love
